dct_description_sm: Relief shown by contours, spot heights, and hachures. Copied from maps originally published by the Survey of Egypt and reissued by the British War Office Geographical Section and the U.S. Army Map Service. Shows two classes of railroads, five classes of roads or tracks and five types of internal boundaries. Set includes  sheets issued by British Middle East Forces (M.D.R. 466) with or without series designation Provisional G.S.G.S. 4085;  "Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, Department of the Army"--All sheets. Some sheets: "reproduced by 512 FD. survey Coy., R.E., ME." Index to adjacent sheets and Markaz boundaries in margin.
dct_creator_sm: Great Britain. War Office. General Staff. Geographical Section
